-- Cartier CEO Doesn’t See Luxury Bubble Forming, L’Hebdo Reports
-- B y   D e r m o t   D o h e r t y
-- 2012-01-11T16:48:43Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-11/cartier-ceo-doesn-t-see-luxury-bubble-forming-l-hebdo-reports.html
Cartier  Chief Executive Officer
Bernard Fornas doesn’t see a bubble forming in the luxury goods
industry, L’Hebdo reported.  Cartier will have a space in a new luxury store being
opened in Paris by parent company  Cie. Financiere Richemont SA (CFR) ,
L’Hebdo reported in an e-mailed preview of an interview with
Fornas to be published in tomorrow’s magazine. Many of the
customers are expected to be from  Asia , according to Fornas.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Dermot Doherty in Geneva at 
 ddoherty9@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Sara Marley at   smarley1@bloomberg.net  